George Wainaina from Majengo estate, Thika, beat 500 boda boda cyclists to emerge the winner of the inaugural Thika Town Boda Boda race on Saturday.The race was organised by Thika Town MP Alice Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a who gave each of the first five cyclists a new Sh130,000 motorcycle.Wainaina said the motorcycle would ease his work and increase his income.Wainaina, who plies his trade at U-shop Thika, clocked 45 minutes after a gruelling 25km race, while Samuel Kimani came second in 49 minutes.